2. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper involves numerical methods for approximating the nonlinear Fourier spectrum of truncated multi-soliton pulses. 
3. cs.SI (Systems and Control): The paper deals with the control of multi-soliton pulses in optical fiber transmission systems. 
4. cs.PH (Physics): The paper involves the study of the Nonlinear Schroedinger Equation, which is a topic in physics. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper involves the development of algorithms for finding the eigenvalues of the discrete spectrum from the continuous spectrum.
